'''''GSF Development Driller II''''' is a fifth generation, [[Vanuatu]]-[[flag of convenience|flagged]] [[dynamic positioning]] [[semi-submersible]] ultra-deepwater drilling rig owned and operated by [[Transocean]]. The vessel is capable of drilling in water depths up to {{convert|7500|ft|abbr=on}} with drilling depth of {{convert|35000|ft|abbr=on}}, upgradeable to {{convert|37500|ft|abbr=on}}.<ref name=gsfdd2>{{cite web|title=GSF ''Development Driller II'' |url=http://www.deepwater.com/fw/main/GSF-Development-Driller-II-199C17.html?LayoutID=17 |publisher=Transocean |accessdate=11 June 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100609163134/http://www.deepwater.com/fw/main/GSF-Development-Driller-II-199C17.html?LayoutID=17 |archivedate=9 June 2010 |df=dmy }}</ref>

''Development Driller II'' was deployed in drilling a relief well on the [[Macondo Prospect]] to stop the [[Deepwater Horizon oil spill|massive oil spill]] caused by the [[Deepwater Horizon drilling rig explosion|explosion and subsequent loss]] of ''[[Deepwater Horizon]]''.<ref name=upstream170510>{{cite news | author=Staff and wire writers | url=http://www.upstreamonline.com/live/article215111.ece | title=Second Macondo relief well under way | work= Upstream Online | date=17 May 2010 | accessdate=11 June 2010}}</ref>

